{"type":"message","id":"f7c6b399","parentId":"10be05be","timestamp":"2026-03-08T08:11:25.450Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1ba8ca1386874df0b51fbb65","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: kurultai-reflection\ndescription: Executes the hourly Kurultai reflection process. Gathers task metrics, chat logs, error logs, and pending hypotheses. Orchestrates sequential agent meta-reflections. Evaluates past hypotheses, updates system files, proposes new hypotheses, and generates a final summary report.\n---\n\n# Kurultai Hourly Reflection Workflow\n\nThis skill orchestrates a native AI meta-reflection for all OpenClaw agents. It forces the system to observe its own failures, validate its past architectural hypotheses, and iteratively rewrite its own operating instructions over time.\n\n## Step 1: Gather System Telemetry\nExecute the following Python scripts to retrieve the system state:\n1. `python3 scripts/fetch_metrics.py` (Neo4j task stats for the last hour)\n2. `python3 scripts/fetch_vitals.py` (Time-series trend analysis of system health and queues over the last hour)\n3. `python3 scripts/fetch_heartbeats.py` (Agent self-reported statuses and \"unfinished business\" from the 30-minute heartbeats)\n4. `python3 scripts/fetch_chat_logs.py` (Chat activity for the last 2 hours)\n5. `python3 scripts/fetch_error_logs.py` (Critical system errors and stack traces from the last hour)\n6. `python3 scripts/manage_hypotheses.py list` (Pending architectural hypotheses from previous hours)\n\n## Step 1.5: System Liveness Gate (Triage Mode)\n**Before proceeding to agent reflections, evaluate system health:**\n\n```python\n# Pseudocode for triage decision\ntotal_completions = sum(metrics[agent]['completed'] for agent in agents)\nerror_count = error_logs['total_critical_events']\nhas_heartbeats = heartbeats is not None and len(heartbeats) > 0\n\nif total_completions == 0 and error_count > 30 and not has_heartbeats:\n    # SYSTEM DOWN - Enter triage mode\n    SKIP_FULL_REFLECTION = True\nelse:\n    SKIP_FULL_REFLECTION = False\n```\n\n**If TRIAGE MODE is triggered:**\n- Skip the 5-agent sequential reflection loop (saves time/tokens)\n- Run a focused diagnostic using only Temujin (Dev) and Ogedei (Ops) reflections\n- Output a \"System Down\" report with a prioritized fix checklist\n- Log a hypothesis automatically: \"System entered triage mode - investigating root cause\"\n\n**If system is healthy:**\n- Proceed to Step 2 with all 5 agent reflections\n\n## Step 2: Agent Reflections & Meta-Reflection (Sequential via Claude Code or Fallback)\n\n**If TRIAGE MODE is active (from Step 1.5):**\nOnly run reflections for **Temujin (Dev)** and **Ogedei (Ops)** with a focused diagnostic prompt:\n```bash\nbash pty:true command:\"claude -p 'SYSTEM IN TRIAGE MODE. Act as [Agent]. System shows 0 completions, high errors, no heartbeats. Focus exclusively on: 1. Identify the ONE root cause to fix first. 2. Provide exact commands to restore service. 3. Skip general suggestions.'\"\n```\n\n**If system is healthy (normal mode):**\nFor EACH of the following agents, use **Claude Code** to execute their reflection. You must pass the gathered telemetry from Step 1 into the prompt. Use your bash execution tool with PTY mode to run:\n\n```bash\n# For each agent, run Claude Code with their reflection prompt\nbash pty:true command:\"claude -p 'Act as [Agent Name], [Agent Role]. Review the following system telemetry: [Insert Telemetry]. Generate a short, insightful meta-reflection on the system architecture. 1. Review error logs for root causes. 2. Analyze task routing/completion. 3. Formulate specific, actionable suggestions for Kublai to improve the system. 4. Brainstorm one specific way to improve this kurultai-reflection skill itself.'\"\n```\n\n**Fallback (if Claude Code/Gemini CLI unavailable):**\nIf the external AI CLI fails (model not found, API error, etc.), generate the agent reflections yourself using your native capabilities. Act as each agent role and produce concise reflections based on the telemetry. This ensures the reflection workflow completes even when external tools are unavailable.\n\nCollect the stdout output from each Claude Code execution (or your own generated reflections) and keep them in your context for the final report.\n\n**Roles:**\n- **temujin**: Developer (code, infrastructure, bugs)\n- **mongke**: Researcher (web research)\n- **chagatai**: Writer (documentation, content)\n- **jochi**: Analyst (testing, security, error analysis)\n- **ogedei**: Ops (monitoring, failover, cron jobs)\n\n*Note: Do not write these individual reflections to disk. Keep them in your context for the final report.*\n\n**Claude Code Configuration:**\n- Location: `/opt/homebrew/bin/claude` (v2.1.66)\n- Auth: OAuth (claude.ai Max subscription)\n- Skills: 76 installed (use relevant agent skills)\n- Always use `pty:true` for interactive CLI\n\n## Step 2.5: Persistent Issue Tracking (Escalation at 3 Reports)\n\n**Track critical issues across reflections and escalate when unresolved:**\n\n```bash\n# Check for issues appearing in 3+ consecutive reflections\nbash pty:true command:\"python3 scripts/persistent-issues.py check-escalations\"\n```\n\n**For each critical issue identified in telemetry or agent reflections:**\n1. Add/update issue in tracker:\n   ```bash\n   bash pty:true command:\"python3 scripts/persistent-issues.py add 'Issue description' --agent <responsible_agent>\"\n   ```\n2. The script automatically:\n   - Creates new issue with report_count=1, OR\n   - Increments report_count for existing similar issue\n   - Sets escalation_required=true when report_count >= 3\n\n**When escalation_required=true:**\n- Mark issue as ESCALATION in final report\n- Auto-create CRITICAL priority task for responsible agent:\n  ```bash\n  # Create task file in agent's task directory\n  echo \"ESCALATION: {issue_description} (unresolved for {report_count} reports)\" > /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/tasks/critical-{timestamp}.md\n  ```\n- Block reflection completion until Kublai acknowledges escalation\n- Add to Kublai Actions: \"ESCALATION: {issue} - task created for {agent}\"\n\n**Script Location:** `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/persistent-issues.py`\n\n**If TRIAGE MODE is active (from Step 1.5):**\nOnly run reflections for **Temujin (Dev)** and **Ogedei (Ops)** with a focused diagnostic prompt:\n```bash\nbash pty:true command:\"claude -p 'SYSTEM IN TRIAGE MODE. Act as [Agent]. System shows 0 completions, high errors, no heartbeats. Focus exclusively on: 1. Identify the ONE root cause to fix first. 2. Provide exact commands to restore service. 3. Skip general suggestions.'\"\n```\n\n**If system is healthy (normal mode):**\nFor EACH of the following agents, use **Claude Code** to execute their reflection. You must pass the gathered telemetry from Step 1 into the prompt. Use your bash execution tool with PTY mode to run:\n\n```bash\n# For each agent, run Claude Code with their reflection prompt\nbash pty:true command:\"claude -p 'Act as [Agent Name], [Agent Role]. Review the following system telemetry: [Insert Telemetry]. Generate a short, insightful meta-reflection on the system architecture. 1. Review error logs for root causes. 2. Analyze task routing/completion. 3. Formulate specific, actionable suggestions for Kublai to improve the system. 4. Brainstorm one specific way to improve this kurultai-reflection skill itself.'\"\n```\n\n**Fallback (if Claude Code/Gemini CLI unavailable):**\nIf the external AI CLI fails (model not found, API error, etc.), generate the agent reflections yourself using your native capabilities. Act as each agent role and produce concise reflections based on the telemetry. This ensures the reflection workflow completes even when external tools are unavailable.\n\nCollect the stdout output from each Claude Code execution (or your own generated reflections) and keep them in your context for the final report.\n\n**Roles