 Compliance\" section\n   - Format:\n     ```markdown\n     ## Rule Compliance - {timestamp}\n     - Rule: \"{full rule text}\"\n     - Status: VIOLATION | COMPLIANT\n     - Evidence: {specific log entries, timestamps, task IDs}\n     ```\n\n5. **Include in final report:**\n   - Add \"Rule Violations\" section if any found\n   - Format: \"**Rule Violations:** {agent}: {rule summary}\"\n\n**Example Check (Temujin):**\n```\nRule: \"WHEN heartbeat fires AND no inbound task exists THEN pull oldest blocked item from MEMORY.md\"\nCheck: \n  - Heartbeat fired? YES (09:00, 09:30)\n  - Task queue empty? YES\n  - MEMORY.md task pulled? NO\n  - Result: VIOLATION\n```\n\n## Step 4: Kublai's Initiative (Self-Improvement Loop)\nStill acting as **Kublai**, ask yourself: *\"What proactive change will I make to the system right now to improve stability, efficiency, or capability?\"*\n\n1. **Take Action:** Execute the change using your tools (e.g., modifying a script, tweaking a cron job, adjusting a config file).\n2. **Git Commit:** If you modify any system scripts or codebase files, you MUST commit the change to Git with a descriptive message.\n3. **Record Hypothesis:** Log your action and your expected outcome into Neo4j using `python3 scripts/manage_hypotheses.py create \"<Action Taken>\" \"<Expected Outcome>\"`.\n4. **Update Memory:** If your action represents a permanent change to how the system should operate or how agents should behave, you MUST append a concise rule to the `MEMORY.md` or `ARCHITECTURE.md` file in the workspace root (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/`) so the system remembers it globally.\n5. **Skill Self-Improvement:** If you decide to implement an agent's suggestion to improve this 'kurultai-reflection' skill, use your tools to modify the skill files in `~/.codex/skills/kurultai-reflection` (e.g., `SKILL.md` or scripts). For Claude Code skills, changes take effect immediately. For Gemini skills, package and reinstall: `gemini skills install ~/.codex/skills/kurultai-reflection --scope user`.\n\n## Step 4.5: Idle Agent Task Assignment\n\n**Auto-assign tasks to agents exceeding 4-hour idle threshold:**\n\nFor EACH agent (temujin, mongke, chagatai, jochi, ogedei):\n\n1. **Calculate hours since last task completion:**\n   ```bash\n   # Check agent's memory file for last activity timestamp\n   # Or check task completion logs\n   last_completion=$(grep -r \"Tasks Completed\" /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/memory/*.md | tail -1)\n   hours_idle=$(python3 -c \"from datetime import datetime; print((datetime.now() - datetime.fromisoformat('{last_completion}')).seconds // 3600)\")\n   ```\n\n2. **Check pending tasks:**\n   ```bash\n   pending=$(ls /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/tasks/*.md 2>/dev/null | grep -v '\\.done$' | grep -v '\\.executing$' | wc -l)\n   ```\n\n3. **If hours_idle > 4 AND pending = 0, auto-assign task:**\n   \n   Priority order for task source:\n   1. **MEMORY.md blocked items** (highest priority)\n   2. **Open cron errors** (from tock data)\n   3. **Parse monetization goal backlog** (goal-driven work)\n   \n   ```bash\n   # Create task file\n   cat > /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/tasks/auto-{timestamp}.md << EOF\n   # Auto-Assigned Task (idle >4 hours)\n   \n   **Priority:** normal\n   **Assigned:** $(date -Iseconds)\n   **Reason:** Agent idle for {hours_idle} hours with no pending tasks\n   \n   **Task:** {task_description from source}\n   \n   **Source:** MEMORY.md blocked items | cron errors | Parse goal backlog\n   EOF\n   ```\n\n4. **Log in reflection:**\n   - Add to Kublai Actions: \"Auto-assigned task to {agent} (idle {hours_idle} hours)\"\n   - Include task description in report\n\n**Example Task Sources:**\n- Temujin: \"Fix TypeScript errors in Parse agent services\" (from MEMORY.md)\n- Mongke: \"Research competitor pricing for Parse features\" (from Parse goal)\n- Chagatai: \"Draft content for Parse feature announcement\" (from Parse goal)\n- Jochi: \"Analyze error log patterns from